{
  "texts": [
    "The 'black-box' nature of AI makes it more susceptible to hide potential manipulation of the data.",
    "To illustrate the exacerbation of already existing ethical challenges, we highlight the privacy objection.",
    "It is useful to recall that privacy concerns were present in traditional polling (Bulmer 1979).",
    "Survey methods involve asking sensitive questions about respondents' values, emotions, and political preferences, and sometimes about their family or neighbours.",
    "Respondents may not fully understand that they have the right not to answer a specific question, in spite of their general agreement to participate in the survey."
  ]
}